{"title": "What I Believe", "description": "\"The inner working of my soul, which I wish to speak of here, was not the result of a methodical investigation of doctrinal theology, or of the actual texts of the gospel; it was a sudden removal of all that hid the true meaning of the Christian doctrine \u2013 a momentary flash of light, which made everything clear to me.  It was something like that which might happen to a man who, after vainly attempting, by a false plan, to build up a statue out of a confused heap of small pieces of marble, suddenly guesses at the figure they are intended to form by the shape of the largest piece; and then, on beginning to set up the statue, finds his guess confirmed by the harmonious joining in of the various pieces.\" (Extract from Chapter 1)", "duration": 28730, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "217", "name": "Leo Tolstoy"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt9/What_I_Believe_1105.jpg", "copyright_year": "1886", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "David Barnes"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "David Barnes"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Laurie Anne Walden"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "AnnSterling"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface and Introduction", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whatibelieve_1101_librivox/whatibelieve_00_tolstoy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 440}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whatibelieve_1101_librivox/whatibelieve_01_tolstoy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1158}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whatibelieve_1101_librivox/whatibelieve_02_tolstoy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 855}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 3", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whatibelieve_1101_librivox/whatibelieve_03_tolstoy_64kb.mp3", "duration"